{"lemma":"فَقْرٌ","slug":"فَقْرٌ","root":"ف.ق.ر","root_slug":"ف-ق-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ق-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَقْر","root":"فقر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":10,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":14},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34297"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dig"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pierce, to perforate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dig"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pierce, to perforate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَقَرَ (faqara, “to dig; to pierce”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become poor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"poverty","examples":[{"text":"10th century, Al-Mutanabbi\nوَمَنْ يُنْفِقِ السَّاعَاتِ فِي جَمْعِ مِالِهِ / مَخَافَةَ فَقْرٍ فَٱلَّذِي فَعَلَ الْفَقْرُ\nwaman yunfiqi s-sāʕāti fī jamʕi mi-l-ihi / maḵāfata faqrin fallaḏī faʕala al-faqru","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ascetic life"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"care, sorrow"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to break one's neck or spine"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have pain in the vertebrae from injury or illness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَقَرَ (faqara, “to break one's neck or spine”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَقِرَ (faqira, “to have pain in the vertebrae”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of فِقْرَة (fiqra), فَقْرَة (faqra), and فُقْرَة (fuqra, “vertebra”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/fa.qa.ra/","/faq.qa.ra/","/faqr/","/fa.qu.ra/","/fa.qi.ra/","/fa.qar/","/fi.qar/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34297","headword_ar":"فَقْرٌ","root":"fqr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuqorN","text_ar":"فُقْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same, (S, O, Msb, K,) but the latter is bad, (Lth, TA,) and sometimes they said ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuqurN","text_ar":"فُقُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Poverty, want,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"need; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ginFY","text_ar":"غِنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of a man when he has"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"only"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what suffices for his household,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those who dwell with him and whose maintenance is incumbent on him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K:) [other meanings are indicated by explanations of the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqiyrN","text_ar":"فَقِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.:] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafAaqiru","text_ar":"مَفاَقِرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"needs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said by some to be a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqrN","text_ar":"فَقرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", anomalous, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aAbihu","text_ar":"مَشَابِهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abahN","text_ar":"شَبَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaAmiHu","text_ar":"مَلَامِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamoHapN","text_ar":"لَمْحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or it may be a pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufoqarN","text_ar":"مُفْقَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoqarahu","text_ar":"اَفْقَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufoqirN","text_ar":"مُفْقِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or it has no sing.: (TA:) you say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a A@ll~`hu mafaAqirahu","text_ar":"سَدَّ ا@للّٰهُ مَفَاقِرَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God rendered him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God render him, free from want;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) [lit.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God supplied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God supply, his various needs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wants."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqorN","text_ar":"فَقْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anxiety;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disquietude,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trouble, of mind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuquwrN","text_ar":"فُقُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K, TA:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akaY A_ilayohi","text_ar":"شَكَى اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuquwrahu","text_ar":"فُقُورَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He complained to him of his anxieties;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.:"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2426},{"kind":"text","text":"and it means also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his circumstances,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [for,] accord. to IAar, the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuquwru","text_ar":"فُقُورُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~afosi","text_ar":"النَّفْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uquwruhaA","text_ar":"شُقُورُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqorapN","text_ar":"فَقْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","Lth","TA","MF","ISd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}